{
  "stem": "19969.7",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was district attorney in western Colorado at that time and I couldn't really have added anything to the Nuremberg Trials and I didn't want to be cross-examined about the killing of those guards.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] One of the interesting things is there have been a number of books written about Dachau-- I have three or four up here in my library now-- and some of them are so outlandish that it's incredible.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I have one book says that we killed something like, I think, 545 German soldiers in Dachau.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Well, there wasn't half that many there when we got there in the first place.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The actual body count done by the inspector general I believe was 34.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And some of those were not killed by American soldiers.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Some were killed by these camp trustees, I call them, the inmates.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There were of course armament everywhere.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Rifles-- the Germans dropped their rifles and the inmates killed probably four or five of the-- the 34.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Because-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] --until we got them stopped, they were going to kill every German they could find.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they probably killed maybe four or five, half-- I don't know how many-- half a dozen of the 34 who were killed.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But the inspector general-- if I-- in the report that he made was very meticulous.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He even counted the bullet holes in the wall where my machine gun had killed those 11.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The number he puts us higher than. 11 but what happened was the-- the-- the prisoners themselves caught some Germans and took them to that place and killed them there.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But my men actually-- my machine gunner-- actually killed about 11.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But the numbers vary according to who wrote the book.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
